title: Grateful Dead Live at Greek Theatre, U. Of California on 1986-06-20
lineage: Sony PCM-601ESD > Terratec EWX2496 card > DAW > DSP by Doug Oade tracked (cdwave) and re-flac'ed by Darrin Sacks
description: Midnight Hour-> Mississippi Half Step, El Paso-> West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Candyman, Let It Grow Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band-> Comes A Time-> Drums-> I Need A Miracle-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text: Love this show! Had to make a comment about this particular recording as I have listened to them all on archive.  This is the one to get, amazing amount of detail from the spaced mk2s and the only one that was recorded digitally.  The Playin' jam is like climbing a wall into Comes a Time!
Best Aud source I agree with the previous person on this sounding the best of all sources.  Even all the newer sources.
